# Pull request watch (reviewgate)

When the user cares about PRs, CI, or merging, **do not assume** there are no open PRs.

**CI:** Workflow `PR LLM review` runs on every PR **push** (`synchronize`) and on a **15-minute schedule** when you need to catch missed webhooks. It posts a diff-based LLM comment once per **head SHA** (re-runs after each push). Configure repo secret **`OPENAI_API_KEY`** (optional repo variables `OPENAI_MODEL`, `OPENAI_BASE_URL`). Fork PRs are skipped (token cannot comment).

For a deeper pass than CI, still do this manually:

1. Run: `gh pr list --repo leo-aa88/reviewgate --state open --json number,title,url`
2. For each open PR, fetch the diff (`gh pr diff <number> --repo leo-aa88/reviewgate`) and review against project standards: strict typing (no silent `Any`), Google-style docstrings on public APIs, file size (non-test under 500 LOC preferred, max 600), modularity, no compat fallbacks without agreement, no magic literals without names, correctness and tests, concurrency safety, KISS/DRY, SOLID/clean code.
3. Post **at most one** substantive comment per PR via `gh pr comment`: tie feedback to **specific files/hunks** (or cite diff context), list concrete change requests or approve with reasons. Do **not** post generic checklist-only comments that ignore the patch.

If `gh` is unavailable or the user is not authenticated, say so and stop after listing what you would have checked.
